article_title: May 16, 2016: NJTV News with Mary Alice Williams
article_text:
Atlantic City remains in limbo. Awaiting a deal to stave off bankruptcy. At least warring legislators are back on speaking terms.

The race to replace Christie is on. Former U.S. ambassador to Germany, Democrat Phil Murphy is first to announce he’s running.

Christie is touring sensational schools, including a charter whose student achievement is out of this world.

President Obama’s commencement address at Rutgers. Part Jersey pride. Part political shots at a presumptive Republican candidate.

Obamacare is flourishing in New Jersey. Senators adding millions more in funding to cover tens of thousands of under-insured.

And the question: He won the Jeopardy Teachers Tournament and its $100,000 prize. The answer? Who is …
